summary: Workers are seeking "better wages, a stronger pension, and to recoup an unpaid arbitration award".

headline: KDP Q1 Earnings Call: Energy Drinks, Innovation, and Pricing Actions Drive Outperformance
summary: Beverage company Keurig Dr Pepper (NASDAQ:KDP) reported Q1 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 4.8% year on year to $3.64 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.42 per share was 9.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
